Chelidonia (cf. Pseudapul. LXXIII, Diosc. II 211) erundina III 555, 34; 556, 34; 50; 588, 68; 590, 3; 609, 37; 611, 3; 620, 55. erundinaria siue Martialis III 537, 18. octonis (ὀθόνιον) III 593, 37; 615, 6. odone III 571, 39. ortonion III 571, 49. rizas III 575, 23. rita III 575, 14. melion III 569, 3. ortantropo III 570, 58. pandiosradia (pandios radix) III 573, 22. pyoniagrates III 573, 24 (paeonia agrestis? piron agreste Stadler). Cf. III 541, 45; 572, 18. taurion III 578, 59. leucia III 555, 2 (= glaucium). laucia III 619, 30. Cf. odonis id est 
celenodia III 627, 23; 
crundenita crenorogo III 544, 50.

Corporeum est quod habet corpus, ut animal, homo, 
corporatum (corporale?) quod sine corpore est, sed repperitur in corpore, ut albedo, nigredo; 
incorporatum (incorporeum?) quod caret corpore V 617, 32 + 33.
